WEBVTT

00:05:29.121 --> 00:05:32.020
They fly thousands of miles
over the Gulf of Mexico.

00:05:32.044 --> 00:05:34.950
And where do they go? Where do they land?

00:05:35.474 --> 00:05:37.990
Right back in the same tree.

00:05:38.686 --> 00:05:39.836
That's nuts.

00:05:40.151 --> 00:05:43.498
This is a bird the size
of a tennis ball --

00:05:43.522 --> 00:05:45.199
I mean, that's crazy!

00:05:45.223 --> 00:05:47.773
I used a GPS to get here today,

00:05:47.797 --> 00:05:49.464
and this is my hometown.

00:05:49.488 --> 00:05:50.759
(Laughter)

00:05:50.783 --> 00:05:51.940
It's crazy.

00:05:52.374 --> 00:05:56.064
So what happens, then, when this bird
flies over the Gulf of Mexico

00:05:56.088 --> 00:05:57.956
into Central America for the winter

00:05:57.980 --> 00:06:00.421
and then the spring rolls around
and it flies back,